  "translations": {
    "en": "So the Prophet (peace be upon him and his family) looked at him angrily, then said: Woe to you, O youth! Are your sins greater, or your Lord? So the youth fell on his face saying: Glory be to my Lord! Nothing is greater than my Lord. My Lord is greater, O Prophet of Allah, than every great thing. So the Prophet (peace be upon him and his family) said: Can anyone other than the Great Lord forgive the great sin?! The youth said: No, by Allah, O Messenger of Allah. Then the youth went silent. So the Prophet (peace be upon him and his family) said to him: Woe to you, O youth! Will you not tell me of one of your sins?",
